3-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESkechers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20addressed%20a%20letter%20to%20Trump%20urging%20him%20to%20protect%20their%20goods%20from%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20industry%20is%20uniquely%20vulnerable%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ffdra.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F04%2FApril-29-Footwear-POTUS-Letter.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20states.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20some%20of%20the%20highest%20tariff%20rates%20already%20in%20place%E2%80%94especially%20on%20children's%20and%20low-cost%20shoes%E2%80%94these%20new%20tariffs%20are%20simply%20unsustainable.%20They%20won't%20bring%20manufacturing%20back%2C%20but%20they%20will%20hurt%20families%20at%20the%20register.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20calls%20the%20situation%20an%20%26quot%3Bemergency%20that%20requires%20immediate%20action%20and%20attention%2C%26quot%3B%20warning%20that%20US%20footwear%20workers%20and%20consumers%20will%20suffer%2C%20citing%20concerns%20about%20imminent%20footwear%20job%20losses%2C%20added%20costs%20for%20consumers%2C%20and%20reduced%20consumer%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20coalition%20of%20manufacturers%2C%20brands%2C%20and%20retailers%20argued%20that%2C%20unlike%20many%20other%20goods%2C%20shoes%20already%20face%20some%20of%20the%20highest%20import%20taxes%20in%20the%20US%20tariff%20code%2C%20with%20rates%20hitting%2020%25%2C%2037.5%25%2C%20or%20even%20higher%2C%20particularly%20on%20children's%20shoes%20and%20lower-priced%20footwear%20favored%20by%20working%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20highlighted%20that%20many%20companies%20are%20already%20grappling%20with%20how%20to%20pay%20the%20sudden%2C%20unforeseen%20tariff%20costs%20on%20merchandise%20ordered%20months%20ago%20that%20is%20only%20now%20arriving%20at%20US%20ports.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20inability%20to%20pay%20for%20these%20immediate%20and%20unforeseen%20additional%20tariffs%20places%20many%20US%20footwear%20businesses%20at%20imminent%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20broad%20tariffs%20affecting%20everyday%20consumer%20goods%2C%20the%20footwear%20executives%20suggested%20a%20%26quot%3Bmore%20targeted%20approach%26quot%3B%20focused%20on%20strategic%20items%20would%20better%20serve%20national%20security%20interests%20without%20inflicting%20%26quot%3Bunnecessary%20pain%20on%20American%20families.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20concludes%20with%20a%20clear%20request%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20respectfully%20ask%20you%20to%20remove%20footwear%20from%20any%20reciprocal%20tariff%20regime.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadidas-says-tariffs-are-going-to-make-sneakers-more-expensive-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAdidas%20warned%20on%20Tuesday%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20sweeping%20tariffs%20could%20drive%20up%20the%20costs%20of%20all%20its%20products%20in%20the%20US%2C%20as%20the%20company%20is%20reliant%20on%20imports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20we%20currently%20cannot%20produce%20almost%20any%20of%20our%20products%20in%20the%20US%2C%20these%20higher%20tariffs%20will%20eventually%20cause%20higher%20costs%20for%20all%20our%20products%20for%20the%20US%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20CEO%20Bj%C3%B8rn%20Gulden%20said.y.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffootwear-brands-urge-trump-to-exempt-shoes-from-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746286006000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68160f3c3fe8d3928364ddae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffootwear-brands-urge-trump-to-exempt-shoes-from-tariffs-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shoe%20brands%20like%20Nike%20and%20Adidas%20said%20that%20they%20are%20%26quot%3Buniquely%20vulnerable%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20impact%20of%20Trump's%20trade%20wa